                <h2>What is the New York City Subway?</h2>
                <p>It is a rail or metro system, or, in official words, a rapid transit system in New York City. The network serves the Boroughs of Manhattan, Brooklyn, Queens, and the Bronx. The New York City government is the owner of the MTA. However, the rapid transit is on lease to the New York City Transit Authority, which is an affiliate company of the state-run Metropolitan Transportation Authority.</p>
                <h3> World’s Oldest Public Transit Systems</h3>
                <p>The New York MTA opened on October 27, 1994, and it is the world’s oldest public transit system, which is the most used transit system. Right now, there are more than 472 stations in operation. New York MTA services are working 24 hours every day, and the New York City subway is the busiest rapid transit system in the Western World and Western Hemisphere.  This rail system is also the world’s most extended system and contains around 248 miles or 399 km of routes.</p>
